<?xml version="1.0" encoding="UTF-8" standalone="no"?><?Xpress productLine="ncc-clause" ?><clause xmlns:xt="urn:xpressauthor:trackchanges" id="_b967e065-2d31-474a-8504-14456236cc1c" outputclass="ncc-clause" variation="NSW"><meta><facet building="Class 1a"/><facet building="Class 1b"/><facet building="Class 10a"/><facet building="Class 10b"/><facet building="Class 10c"/></meta><sptc>D2D9</sptc><title id="_70de8378-5602-43d0-a415-aeee202edeac">Width of doorways in exits or paths of travel to exits</title><archive-num>2019: D1.6, NSW D1.6(f)(vi)</archive-num><subclause id="_8a8e71bb-0c40-42be-97a7-714a3b183f50" outputclass="subclause"><title id="_3c9e396d-ac08-40c7-ba96-adf69954b49f">SubClause</title><num>1</num><p>In a <xref format="dita" href="/tmp/QppServer/Publishing/5e2c1f63-e589-4ce1-95e8-5c3e286a7aff/1432_4.0.0.xml#_af6fde9f-147d-4782-8b85-42044e80fd42" id="_44980316-84c7-40b8-b39b-c5bda9b6f452" scope="local" type="abcb-glossentry">required</xref> <xref format="dita" href="/tmp/QppServer/Publishing/5e2c1f63-e589-4ce1-95e8-5c3e286a7aff/1263_2.3.0.xml#_9712f630-8cf7-401b-b1cc-ae0be4485915" id="_7eb8d3fd-7599-4789-b469-696a0bb49b4a" scope="local" type="abcb-glossentry">exit</xref> or path of travel to an <xref format="dita" href="/tmp/QppServer/Publishing/5e2c1f63-e589-4ce1-95e8-5c3e286a7aff/1263_2.3.0.xml#_9712f630-8cf7-401b-b1cc-ae0be4485915" id="_379173d1-e2a4-451a-b3a9-04c240cce24e" scope="local" type="abcb-glossentry">exit</xref>, the unobstructed width of a doorway must be not less than—</p><ol outputclass="alpha"><li id="_ccfaa395-c0a4-4b03-8ab4-58de25a98069">in <xref format="dita" href="/tmp/QppServer/Publishing/5e2c1f63-e589-4ce1-95e8-5c3e286a7aff/1393_4.0.0.xml#_63b56568-e9c9-425f-8456-a332503c9520" id="_6e4c2930-d451-46e6-8d19-fe633063a473" scope="local" type="abcb-glossentry">patient care areas</xref> through which patients would normally be transported in beds—<ol><li>if the doorway provides access to, or from, a corridor of width—<ol><li>less than 2.2 m — 1200 mm; or</li><li>2.2 m or greater — 1070 mm; and</li></ol></li><li>where the doorway referred to in (i) is fitted with two leaves and one leaf is secured in the closed position in accordance with <xref format="dita" href="/tmp/QppServer/Publishing/5e2c1f63-e589-4ce1-95e8-5c3e286a7aff/1705_1.8.0.xml#_16c6bcbd-a61a-48fe-912b-b0126f901b3d" id="_9d94bf0d-f106-4c93-80a1-5491fd033f10" referencetype="Text" scope="local" synctargettext="false" type="subclause">D3D26(3)(e)</xref>, the other leaf must permit an unobstructed opening not less than 800 mm wide; or</li></ol></li><li id="_482061e7-2348-4a09-b67f-54fdddef032c">in <xref format="dita" href="/tmp/QppServer/Publishing/5e2c1f63-e589-4ce1-95e8-5c3e286a7aff/1393_4.0.0.xml#_63b56568-e9c9-425f-8456-a332503c9520" id="_6a51070d-ebb9-4c32-bd51-0420aceba64b" scope="local" type="abcb-glossentry">patient care areas</xref> in a <xref format="dita" href="/tmp/QppServer/Publishing/5e2c1f63-e589-4ce1-95e8-5c3e286a7aff/1340_2.0.0.xml#_45cfdc7e-cb0d-4318-95cc-462e079e9b9c" id="_1ab334c1-91df-4cf8-b80f-ccf1c9717c7a" scope="local" type="abcb-glossentry">horizontal exit</xref> — 1250 mm; or</li><li id="_3799c59e-b878-4a88-9c96-8585a483038f">the unobstructed width of each <xref format="dita" href="/tmp/QppServer/Publishing/5e2c1f63-e589-4ce1-95e8-5c3e286a7aff/1263_2.3.0.xml#_9712f630-8cf7-401b-b1cc-ae0be4485915" id="_1c61167b-7a5f-4640-bd6d-fcd50695699f" scope="local" type="abcb-glossentry">exit</xref> provided to comply with <xref format="dita" href="/tmp/QppServer/Publishing/5e2c1f63-e589-4ce1-95e8-5c3e286a7aff/1541_1.17.0.xml#_f7dc307f-c158-4f1b-9474-45cc238a8f05" id="_f01d7eed-1182-446f-92d6-868ae15562bb" scope="local" type="subclause">D2D8(1)</xref>, <xref format="dita" href="/tmp/QppServer/Publishing/5e2c1f63-e589-4ce1-95e8-5c3e286a7aff/1541_1.17.0.xml#_b267d0a0-2c65-448a-99bc-c6d1a0eb4b57" id="_550d5158-e870-455d-9ff5-855ce4b8f473" scope="local" type="subclause">(2)</xref>, <xref format="dita" href="/tmp/QppServer/Publishing/5e2c1f63-e589-4ce1-95e8-5c3e286a7aff/1541_1.17.0.xml#_b76f8365-e6ce-499c-8e99-1bfae23417e2" id="_df933c41-0894-4137-b56a-fdb990d92be0" scope="local" type="subclause">(3)</xref> or <xref format="dita" href="/tmp/QppServer/Publishing/5e2c1f63-e589-4ce1-95e8-5c3e286a7aff/1541_1.17.0.xml#_9ba309b3-9ae6-41c7-82e0-22d6c87f7d09" id="_960c219f-b8c5-4a76-8a53-c43511471b16" scope="local" type="subclause">(4)</xref>, minus 250 mm; or</li><li id="_5496b839-f955-4007-99db-f793d104e0fe">in a Class 9c building, 800 mm, except—<ol><li>in <xref format="dita" href="/tmp/QppServer/Publishing/5e2c1f63-e589-4ce1-95e8-5c3e286a7aff/1437_4.0.0.xml#_071db02d-667d-447e-9f1e-8de8c46b9e0e" id="_e2a171e2-3a0d-4288-b582-a8fe093027e7" scope="local" type="abcb-glossentry">resident use areas</xref> the minimum unobstructed width must be 870 mm; and</li><li>for doorways leading from a <xref format="dita" href="/tmp/QppServer/Publishing/5e2c1f63-e589-4ce1-95e8-5c3e286a7aff/1419_4.0.0.xml#_eea79623-bc7d-4ef1-b787-8452b6383ffc" id="_935b307b-6b47-4c36-84e4-15d8ae85e0ec" scope="local" type="abcb-glossentry">public corridor</xref> to a <xref format="dita" href="/tmp/QppServer/Publishing/5e2c1f63-e589-4ce1-95e8-5c3e286a7aff/1473_0.4.0.xml#_d2c89488-8a36-464b-94f6-a91d0f5a6c9c" id="_e8256859-260f-47c9-95ff-04ceacefb3e3" scope="local" type="abcb-glossentry">sole-occupancy unit</xref> the minimum unobstructed width must be 1070 mm; and</li><li>where the doorway is fitted with two leaves and one leaf is secured in the closed position in accordance with <xref format="dita" href="/tmp/QppServer/Publishing/5e2c1f63-e589-4ce1-95e8-5c3e286a7aff/1705_1.8.0.xml#_16c6bcbd-a61a-48fe-912b-b0126f901b3d" id="_94938ac2-5510-44d8-8fb4-bdc9a4345a79" referencetype="Text" scope="local" synctargettext="false" type="subclause">D3D26(3)(e)</xref>, the other leaf must permit an unobstructed opening not less than 870 mm wide in <xref format="dita" href="/tmp/QppServer/Publishing/5e2c1f63-e589-4ce1-95e8-5c3e286a7aff/1437_4.0.0.xml#_071db02d-667d-447e-9f1e-8de8c46b9e0e" id="_31208c21-5146-42e1-895a-989d967039aa" scope="local" type="abcb-glossentry">resident use areas</xref> and 800 mm wide in non-<xref format="dita" href="/tmp/QppServer/Publishing/5e2c1f63-e589-4ce1-95e8-5c3e286a7aff/1437_4.0.0.xml#_071db02d-667d-447e-9f1e-8de8c46b9e0e" id="_fd9b285f-4ffe-4c4d-93cc-c6635ec53882" scope="local" type="abcb-glossentry">resident use areas</xref>; or</li></ol></li><li id="_ba6e08b7-e0b2-4037-be83-5e8f5a7cea15">in a Class 9b building used as an <xref format="dita" href="/tmp/QppServer/Publishing/5e2c1f63-e589-4ce1-95e8-5c3e286a7aff/2451_0.6.0.xml#_410e8de4-5482-4e25-932f-371f1d5d6042" id="_13b90ef8-7c38-44e0-81f3-e9d566941b83" scope="local" type="abcb-glossentry">entertainment venue</xref>—<ol><li>in parts of the building used by the public, the width of the <xref format="dita" href="/tmp/QppServer/Publishing/5e2c1f63-e589-4ce1-95e8-5c3e286a7aff/1432_4.0.0.xml#_af6fde9f-147d-4782-8b85-42044e80fd42" id="_4a6f963e-578f-470f-827b-f6ca63bc7909" scope="local" type="abcb-glossentry">required</xref> <xref format="dita" href="/tmp/QppServer/Publishing/5e2c1f63-e589-4ce1-95e8-5c3e286a7aff/1263_2.3.0.xml#_9712f630-8cf7-401b-b1cc-ae0be4485915" id="_e1ff5767-c6c9-45a5-8935-20310441c5da" scope="local" type="abcb-glossentry">exit</xref> or path of travel, and the unobstructed width of each doorway must not be less than 1 m and not more than 3 m; and</li><li>in other parts of the building, doorways must comply with NSW D2D9; or</li></ol></li><li id="_57ae30dd-2bf4-4fce-9aba-376c6f5148ff">in any other case except where it opens to a <xref format="dita" href="/tmp/QppServer/Publishing/5e2c1f63-e589-4ce1-95e8-5c3e286a7aff/1445_0.13.0.xml#_b30a308f-eb9f-4549-a6c1-19d5f32a5272" id="_415d703f-f426-403e-93d2-2853a793e26c" scope="local" type="abcb-glossentry">sanitary compartment</xref> or bathroom — 750 mm wide.</li></ol></subclause></clause>